<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="231" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1104,2077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,148,1133,1154]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">2</emphasis>
. Leaflets margin sparsely puberule at least near the base and the apex, upper surface glabrous, lower surface sparsely puberule with a denser indumentum along the midrib, near the base and the apex; tuft of trichomes on the lower surface of the leaflets present, unilateral 
<emphasis box="[304,1282,1192,1213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">...................................................................................................................................................................</emphasis>
2. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rizzini &amp; Heringer" authorityYear="1987" box="[1309,1451,1190,1212]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barbatulum">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1309,1451,1190,1212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">S. barbatulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="231" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1104,2077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,156,1219,1241]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">2’</emphasis>
. Leaflets margin glabrous (except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heringer &amp; Rizzini" authorityYear="1966" box="[537,659,1220,1241]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="confertum">
<emphasis box="[537,659,1220,1241]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">S. confertum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, ciliate), both surfaces glabrous to rarely sparsely pubescent on the lower surface near the insertion of the secondary petiolule (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rizzini &amp; Heringer" authorityYear="1966" box="[655,796,1248,1270]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platyspicum">
<emphasis box="[655,796,1248,1270]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">S. platyspicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or along the midrib (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heringer &amp; Rizzini" authorityYear="1966" box="[1015,1137,1249,1270]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="confertum">
<emphasis box="[1015,1137,1249,1270]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">S. confertum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); tuft of trichomes on the lower surface of the leaflets absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
